Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{2}(chopped into 1cm chunks) (no need to peel).

Pop the sweet potato onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @macaroni{180%g}.

When the oven is hot, roast the sweet potato on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When your water is boiling, stir the macaroni into the pan and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While everything cooks, pick the @sage{1%bunch}(leaves picked and finely chopped) (discard the stalks).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}, then set aside for now.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

While everything cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine the sage, @breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside your sage crumb.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

== Sauce ==

Melt the @butter{20%g} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water{200%ml} for the sauce a little at a time, followed by the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @Dijon mustard{10%g}, @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) and Cheddar. Stir until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add less mustard if you don't love mustard.

== Assembly ==

When the sweet potato is ready, remove it from the oven and turn your #grill{} on to high.

Stir the sweet potato into the sauce along with the cooked macaroni. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer the pasta to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the sage crumb, then pop it under the grill until golden and bubbling, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When ready, share the sweet potato mac and cheese between your serving bowls and get stuck in.

Enjoy!